-- Barwa Surges Most in Year on $3 Billion Financial District Sale
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2011-12-22T06:55:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-22/barwa-surges-most-in-year-on-3-billion-financial-district-sale.html
Barwa Real Estate Co. surged the
most in more than a year after the Qatari developer sold the
Barwa Financial District to state-owned Qatar Petroleum for 11
billion riyals ($3 billion).  The shares rallied 7.3 percent, the most since December
2010, to 31.5 riyals at 9:36 a.m. in Doha trading. The stock is
down 14 percent so far this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
